replies.body:
They got such tailormade items to mitigate weaknesses they have and it's dumb.

Can't dodge cc with your hypermobile kit? {{item:3814}} 
Couldn't land enough abilities to burst? {{item:3147}} 
Don't have enough mobility to roam? {{item:3142}} 
Played with impunity and didn't respect mages' damage? {{item:3156}} 

And yes, every class has items to help them be "better." But these items basically remove key counterplay from assassins or accentuate their strengths to stupid degrees with little tradeoff ({{item:3147}} )

But let's keep saying assassins are unplayable because supports could finally do their jobs and make them use skill to kill the ADC

*Sees whole mathematical formulas and video evidence proving hexdrinker is broken*

"There's no proof this item is broken"

{{sticker:sg-lux-2}}
